content_vision: Ironic and witty self-hating song about how loser I am. Good spirited. Like Radiohead - Creep.
text:
Intro:
let my music take over your mind, let it consume
people think i live a luxurious life, they just see the fun and assume.

Verse 1:
i ain't finished, i got more to say,
we just want all the blue hundreds, stacking up every single day.
baby, you gotta work with me,
'cause it's the 21st century,
and i gotta keep movin' on, can't slow.
gotta get my hitters out, free 'em from the cell,
your latest album got me cheesin', in a spell.
waited for love to come around,

Pre-Chorus 1:
my loyalty to my crew will never sway,
and bring me half back, that's all i gotta say.

Chorus 1:
on memory lane, no more yellow bricks,
you got all them pheromones, and you stayed with me, no tricks.
you look so good, my eyes can't be contained,
girl put it on me, i'll put it on you, call it a fair game.

Verse 2:
saw a dandelion, blowing in the breeze,
through the grapevine i heard my baby girl needs,
gotta get her bills paid, that's the keys.
my darling so it goes, we rise and we fall,
all these bitches wanna fuck me 'cause i made it and they saw
but i stood on that block like meek milly, pushed through the pain
now i'm on top, nobody can bring me down again.
ooh oh oh, got my swag on dummy,

Pre-Chorus 2:
life is crazy the way she did me dirty,
but she gets a bag, ain't that just so flirty?

Chorus 2:
we're the ones who plant and cultivate,
open your mind, don't let it stagnate.
tell my a$ ap killers, we ain't gonna lose,
you hear the shots, we just brush it off, no use,

Bridge:
now watch me as i pull a rabbit out a hat,
proof that i can't be stopped, no denying that.
overseas trips with my squad, got all these foreigns
he said he want a knockout, a good box like pacquiao, no more moaning.

Outro:
i gotta tell him, can't keep it in
shoutout to clayhead, keepin' it real within.

active_struct.name: The Climactic Chaos
attrs: has a strong and captivating intro
includes a prechorus, building anticipation for the chorus
allows for repeated chorus usage and bridge variation
ends on a final chorus for a sense of closure and conclusion

struct_suggs.name: The Ebb and Flow
attrs: follows a straightforward verse-prechorus-chorus pattern
allows for repeated use of the chorus, making it catchy and easy to remember
includes a bridge to add variation to the song
ends on a final chorus, providing a satisfying conclusion to the song

struct_suggs.name: The Instrumental Journey
attrs: has a strong and attention-grabbing intro
includes multiple verses and choruses, making it suitable for a longer song
features a solo section (S), adding an instrumental element to the song
ends with a final chorus for a sense of closure

struct_suggs.name: The Alternating Anthem
attrs: has room for two distinct verse-chorus progressions
includes a prechorus, building anticipation for the chorus
allows for repeated use of the chorus, creating a memorable hook
includes a bridge for variation and added depth to the song

struct_suggs.name: The Continuous Climb
attrs: has a strong and engaging intro
includes a prechorus, gradually building up to the catchy chorus
has multiple verses and choruses for a longer song
features an instrumental section (IN) and ends on a final chorus

struct_suggs.name: The Melodic Mastery
attrs: includes a verse, chorus, and bridge, providing a balanced song structure
features an instrumental section (IN) and a theme melody (T), adding musical interest
allows for two distinct choruses, making it easy for listeners to remember and sing along
ends on a final chorus, creating a satisfying conclusion to the song

attrs: begins with a catchy chorus, immediately grabbing the listener's attention
features an instrumental section (IN) and a theme melody (T), adding musical interest and variation
includes a prechorus and bridge, creating a dynamic structure
ends on a final chorus in the outro for a satisfying conclusion

struct_suggs.name: The Dynamic Distance
attrs: has a strong and attention-grabbing intro
includes a verse, chorus, and prechorus, providing a balanced structure
features an instrumental section (IN) before the final verse
ends on a final chorus, providing a sense of closure to the song

struct_suggs.name: The Repetitive Rhythm
attrs: follows a simple verse-chorus pattern, making it easy to follow
includes an instrumental section (IN) for variation and interest
has room for two distinct choruses, creating a catchy hook
ends on a final chorus, providing a satisfying conclusion to the song

struct_suggs.name: The Instrumental Interlude
attrs: has an attention-grabbing intro
includes a balanced combination of verse, chorus, and instrumental section (IN)
features a solo (T) for an added musical element
ends on a final chorus for a sense of closure and conclusion

Intro:
got my head held high, and my goals are in sight,
rocking sl denim, they feelin' my vibe tonight.

Verse 1:
to feel this luxury, oh it's surreal,
but you can't afford me, just listen to my maybach music for a reveal.
lost in the abyss, too far gone, tryna find a way out
if you wanna join us again, gotta leave your doubts.
all these haters tryna bring us down, they wanna see us fail
but we ain't kidding, we'll rise above, slay like a daily sale.
you know that's where we gotta be,
we came a long way to be finally free.

Pre-Chorus 1:
we gonna getchyall, turn up the heat,
we bout to have a party, wild and free.

Chorus 1:
i can see you craving that high, you like the smoke
gotta keep pushing, never gonna stop, i gotta get on
like john wayne, gonna ride into the sunset, blaze my own trail.
we've been in the game for a minute now,

Verse 2:
i could've been one of the greats, best running back never seen,
but i chose a different path, i chose to rob my mama's friend, if you know what i mean.
i'm up in my zone, can't avoid the hurt,
but i let it fly right into the fucking sky, let it spurt.
call me old school, i ain't hip to all this modern game
but when i see you, baby girl, i know we're one and the same.
every day i put my mind on my money,
got bars like a felon, ain't no stopping me.

Pre-Chorus 2:
at the same time, i'm feeling so high,
a licky boom boom down, reaching for the sky.

Chorus 2:
there's freedom within, even in the rain,
we still gonna rise, no need for pain.
let me make it clear, let me know if you're hearing me,
we out here chasing our dreams, can you feel the energy?

Bridge:
microphone check 2, it's so sweet, yeah
any rapper wanna test, they can get it any day.
it makes you fly to the sky, take that leap of faith,
and you set it up before it burns, can't let it go to waste,

Outro:
she's got that baby blue in her eyes,
but don't let her fool ya, she knows all the lies,

Verse 1:
you've achieved what they all said you never could,
now they're just fronting, misunderstood.
you used to be my ride or die, my man, my realest,
but now they bring them sticks out, you running like a squealer, that's the realest.
she's got that baby blue in her eyes,
but don't let her fool ya, she knows all the lies,
so better watch your back, play it cool, don't make her wise.
there's freedom within, even in the rain,

Chorus:
i could've been one of the greats, best running back never seen,
but i chose a different path, i chose to rob my mama's friend, if you know what i mean.
microphone check 2, it's so sweet, yeah
any rapper wanna test, they can get it any day.

Verse 2:
got a trini man, he knows how to make it
he can tell you all about it, done it with headie.
all these haters tryna bring us down, they wanna see us fail
but we ain't kidding, we'll rise above, slay like a daily sale.
don't look away, keep your eyes locked on mine,
2012 freak shit, we ahead of our time.
to feel this luxury, oh it's surreal,
but you can't afford me, just listen to my maybach music for a reveal.

Intro:
we could take all night, just you and me
i'll make you lose your mind, and then you'll see.

Verse 1:
you can go on with your life, baby girl,
nearly killed me with your love, it's like a whirl.
living wilder than life, never slowing down
burning down the highway, no limit, we own this town.
they say you can't change fate, but i don't believe in that,
with hard work and faith, i am my own god, ain't no turning back.
all i wanna do is be successful, yeah
people showin' love and payin' me respect, that's all i ask.

Pre-Chorus 1:
you think you're a god, but you ain't no divine
all the stars may shine, but they can't save you from your decline.

Chorus 1:
got two cute freaks, but they'll cost you more than twenty bones,
i must be the shit, and he saves me from these heartless clones.
do you wanna ride with me outside,
underneath the purple sky, let's fly.

Verse 2:
i found my purpose, my drive, my passion, my flow,
now they calling me cocky, but that's just how it goes.
i've been through it all, never ran from the pain,
never backing down, always up for a fight in the game.
she want it in her tummy, that's what she said,
and i'ma get you back to the crib, lay back and relax in bed.
funny how love always ends in pain,
but it's like, nah mean, still gotta play the game.

Pre-Chorus 2:
them things never had nothin', they don't mean a thing,
and no one's gonna stand in my way, i'll do my own thing.

Chorus 2:
i don't need no backup, i'll take on the fight
so stand aside, let 'em come, i'll put up a good fight.
they wanna live and die by my side, that's loyalty,
my girl knows it's ride or die, her love is royalty.

Bridge:
i waited on you for so damn long,
you deserve the world, everything you want, can't do you wrong.
we're living life, this is the place to be,
no need to dwell on the past, got a cup of lean to set us free.

Outro:
you didn't know he was playin' me, sellin' hooks behind my back,
but when i found out, i had to tell you, you know i had to say it,

Verse 1:
i must be the shit, cause i got so many girls,
can't keep track, got me in a whirl.
spitting successful lyrics, i never fail to impress,
you lay out the foundation, i'll turn it into success.
living the high life, don't need much, don't need diamond chains,
looks run in the family, can't change it, that's just how it remains.
you were my man, from last night's lit party,
i got so unlucky, damn, where's my bacardi?

Pre-Chorus 1:
we've overcome so much in this life,
and now we're just being admired, inside.

Chorus 1:
lost my first love, she left me in the rain,
now i'm standing strong, never gonna feel pain.
abandoning compassion for wealth and fame,
all of my change goes to keeping my name.

Verse 2:
let me know again, i'm feelin' you tonight,
put it in your mouth, everything's gonna be alright.
feels like i'm on fire, can't control it, can't tame,
i collect these hormones, bossin' up my game.

Pre-Chorus 2:
put em up like a kite, we got nothing to hide
they can't touch us, we're a couple, living in our own ride.

Chorus 2:
late nights hanging out with my crew, laughing till we cry,
and my brother always got my back like a wayans by my side.
just come fly with me, i'll show you the way
i'm a hormone collector, i'll make you sway.

Bridge:
we gettin hella high, livin in the clouds,
switchin it up, just how we know how.
my rhymes hit your brain like a clit,
open your mind, you'll never wanna quit.

Outro:
i'm singing out, can't hold back the strain,
my girl, my love, you can't avoid the pain.

Verse 1:
why do we keep hurting each other, it's such a shame,
when we're supposed to be a couple, united, never estranged.
better take a look at your future, it's darkening fast,
yeah nigga, don't try to hide or mask,
haha, i'll be laughing last.
my dreams are falling apart,
but i keep dancing with this mystery, my heart.
listen to me honey, can you see?

Pre-Chorus 1:
there are feelings left not even we can kill
if you keep thinking that way, we never will

Chorus 1:
my love is like a blessing, so pure and true,
wrapped up in all these numbers, like a barcode, who knew?
these are my introduction lyrics, a taste of what i'm about to do.
she's fierce, chokin' out these haters like a boss,

Verse 2:
it's like someone turned up the heat, we're getting steamy and hot,
making love all over again, can't keep our hands off
and the way we move, it's like we're in our own world,
ain't nobody else's business, we move different, they can't hurl.
you get down, ain't no need to pretend,
why settle for less when she's the 411, my friend?
we keep pushing forward, on into eternity,
living extravagant, always keepin' it fancy.

Pre-Chorus 2:
money team, that's what we call our crew,
and once my homies taste that good p****, they know i'll be true.

Chorus 2:
listen up, baby girl, just know this now,
i'll always hold you close, you're a part of me somehow.
i never had s***, but now i'm living lavish,
while he saw the dark clouds, i saw opportunities to ravish.

Bridge:
can we go, escape the city lights,
he can have your sex, but i'll steal your heart with all my love tonight.
with you i'm addicted, you can make me your drug babe
and when you feel alone, please remember me once more, i'll be your escape.

Verse 1:
feelin' that heat, getting hotter as we go,
but i can't stop now, gotta keep moving through baby blue, you know.
yeah i messed up, ain't no doubt in my mind,
but i'm living life, from a angle you could never find.
your future's looking dim, can't you see the storm clouds brewing,
you know what i stand for, truth and justice pursuing.
we'll run with the gritty, the rough and the raw,
love ain't perfect, that's why the lowlies cry for more.

Pre-Chorus 1:
when it all falls apart, we gotta keep moving,
gotta stay on top, know the competition's grooving.

Chorus 1:
you better back up, don't mess with me,
fucking with my crew will get you six feet deep.
i'm picking up the pieces, playing through the pain,
tell me anything, we got a lot of swag to gain.

Verse 2:
this is what it is, you know the deal,
you calling me baby, but do you wanna for real?
do you wanna come outside, see what's in store,
or you content playing games, never wanting more?
i tried to find a way out, i searched high and low,
but there ain't another way, this life is all i know,
these numbers on my wrist, they're just another barcode.
she puts her head onto my chest, i can feel her heartbeat,

Pre-Chorus 2:
stop overthinking, it's just a waste of time,
instead, go out and play, let your soul shine.

Chorus 2:
i wanna shout it from the rooftops,
tell everybody we're in a love that never stops.
my flow sick, killin' it with each verse,
i leave competition in the hearse.

Bridge:
if i get you, will you be mine forever?
or should i let it be, move on, and just be clever?
my dreams know no bounds, they're limitless
we can navigate through any maze, you know i'm fearless.

Outro:
wanna shout it from the rooftops and let you know
i'm not john wayne, but i'll ride for you, no beef, just love to show.

Verse 1:
in this messed up world, you find so many people are horrible,
but cypress hill keeps me calm, helps me restore my soul,
when i'm with you, all that matters is kissum kissum kissum,
forget the haters, we'll just keep livin' in our own blissdom.
rings like the championships, we're all about that win,
you know what i stand for, never giving in,
we gonna getchyall, rise above and never fall.
it's time to take control, fuck 'em up,

Pre-Chorus 1:
love can be fleeting, just a temporary dream,
but for us, we were meant to be, we make a perfect team.

Chorus 1:
living the dark life, it's tough, it's cold, it's hard, it's unforgiving,
and you gon' show me love, or leave me alone, i ain't kidding.
go ahead, put your weight on me, lay your head
but don't you dare try to rob my mama's friend, she's got enough struggles to contend.

Verse 2:
you played me for a fool, turned my heart into stone
now them boys are bringing out their weapons, no one's gonna leave here alone.
rings like the championships, we're on top of our game,
they gave him 25, but we ain't gonna change,
we bout to have a party, life's too short to be tame.
when you're sad and alone, please remember me once more
even when the sun is shining, i'll be your shelter from the storm.
i gotta cosign, you got that aura of greatness,

Pre-Chorus 2:
oh baby let me come, i'll show you what i got
all my brothers wifed me once they tasted what i brought

Chorus 2:
she buying her man all these luxuries, making my pockets hurt
but i gotta provide for my little girl, i'll do whatever, that's how it works.
love me all of the time, not just when it's easy,
keep that fire blazing, bam bam bam, never feeling queasy.

Bridge:
tell him meet me in the lobby, let's make a deal,
all of my change for his love, just got to be real.
i know sometimes the words i say are too loud,
and we argue all the time, but you keep me grounded,

Outro:
i wasn't supposed to stick around, no sir,
but here i am, keepin' it real and making 'em holler 'whooooa! '
